"{\"uid\": \"jamaicaobserver.com-2024-05-18-olympic-torch-relay-cancelled-violence-hit-new-caledonia\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"PARIS,\\u00a0France\\u00a0(AFP) - Plans for the Olympic torch relay to pass through New Caledonia were cancelled on Saturday after rioting in the French Pacific territory left six people dead, officials announced.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 201, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 72, \"end\": 85, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Caledonia\", \"score\": 0.9999999621121567, \"rank\": 3.7887813440823744e-08, \"text\": \"New Caledonia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Caledonia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Caledonia\"}, {\"begin\": 134, \"end\": 140, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9473086792531759, \"rank\": 0.043313457072159466, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The flame had been scheduled to arrive on June 11 but French Sports Minister Amelie Oudea-Castera said that \\\"priority must be given to a return to calm\\\" in the territory.\", \"from\": 203, \"to\": 373, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 257, \"end\": 263, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9473086792531759, \"rank\": 0.043313457072159466, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I think that everyone understands, given the context, that the priority really is to consolidate the return to public order, and then to appeasement.\", \"from\": 375, \"to\": 525, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Priority to the safety of residents, priority to a return to calm, and priority to the political improvement of the situation.\\\"\", \"from\": 527, \"to\": 655, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Anger is high over a contested voting reform in New Caledonia where hundreds of heavily armed French soldiers and police were on Saturday patrolling the capital city of Noumea.\", \"from\": 657, \"to\": 833, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 705, \"end\": 718, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Caledonia\", \"score\": 0.9999999621121567, \"rank\": 3.7887813440823744e-08, \"text\": \"New Caledonia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Caledonia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Caledonia\"}, {\"begin\": 751, \"end\": 757, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9473086792531759, \"rank\": 0.043313457072159466, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 826, \"end\": 832, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noum\\u00e9a\", \"score\": 0.9994317884213348, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noumea\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noum\\u00e9a\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noum\\u00e9a\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"HOUSE RULES  Comments are closed.\", \"from\": 835, \"to\": 868, \"entities\": []}]}"